      "role": "user",
      "content": "That sounds good, but I'm a bit hesitant about \"simulated\" tests. In the real world, the heat buildup and constant interruptions actually drain them faster than a lab test. If I sign this and we find out the specs are a bit optimistic, it's my head on the block. Are you absolutely certain there's no margin of error here? Like, if we push them to the limit, is it possible they'll drop off before the 24 hours is up?",
